org.emoncms

Class Input

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.emoncms.Input

  • public abstract class Input
extends java.lang.Object
    The Input class is used to communicate with an emoncms webserver and handle input specific actions. An input instance can be used to
    • Post data to the instanced input.
    • Configure logging or other data processing.
    • Get configuration information.

    Inputs hold all their configuration fields in memory, but may be cleared to only hold their ID, node and name by calling clear(). Input methods only need those variables to maintain their functionality and other resources may be released to save memory. Current values for all fields can be retrieved by calling load().
